- @page_title = "Integration in a responsive layout"

%h2= @page_title

:textile
  Thanks to our "JavaScript API":/javascript-api, making your videos scale along with your responsive layout is easy to achieve. In order to do this you have to listen to the browserâ€™s window @resize@ event, and then call the "@sublimevideo.resize@":/javascript-api/methods#resize method when the event is fired.

  h4. HTML Code

  bc(language-markup). <video id="video1" class="responsive" poster="posterframe.jpg" width="640" height="360" preload="none">
    <source src="video.mp4" />
    <source src="video.webm" />
  </video>

  *Notes:*

  * Don't set the _sublime_ @class@ to the @<video>@ element since the video will be prepared through the JS API.
  * We'll use the _responsive_ @class@ in the JavaScript code below.

  h4. JavaScript Code (jQuery)

  The following code will automatically resize all the @<video>@ elements that have the _responsive_ @class@ on page load *and* when the window is resized. Put this code in a @<script>@ element.

  <pre data-line=8,18><code class="language-javascript">var fluidParent, newWidth;

  // Prevents some flickering. For a better efficiency, you may want to put
  // this line in a <script> tag just below your <video> elements.
  $("video.responsive").css('visibility', 'hidden');

  $(document).ready(function() {
    fluidParent = $("#content");
  });

  $(window).resize(function() {
    resizeVideo();
  });

  function resizeVideo() {
    newWidth = fluidParent.width();
    $("video.responsive").each(function(){
      sublimevideo.resize($(this)[0], newWidth, newWidth / (16/9));
    });
  }

  sublimevideo.ready(function(){
    // Prepare all the videos with the "responsive" class
    $("video.responsive").each(function(){
      sublimevideo.prepare($(this)[0]);
    });

    resizeVideo();
  });</code></pre>

  *Line 8.* Replace "content" with the actual @id@ of the container element to which the videos must adapt.
  *Line 18.* Replace "(16/9)" with the actual width/height ratio of your videos.

